Sex ratios differ significantly across Indian states, suggesting that gender imbalance varies by region and is not spread uniformly nationwide.

The female share of population remains below 50 percent in most states, highlighting a persistent imbalance in overall population composition.

Based on this data Southern states show relatively higher Female-to-Male ratios.

Some states continue to show relatively low sex ratios, reflecting persistent gender disparities

These patterns have implications for gender equity, labor force participation, and social policy.
